<!-- API TESTING CONCEPTS -->
<section class="container my-5 p-4 bg-white rounded shadow-sm">
  <h2 class="fw-bold mb-3">API Testing â€“ Complete Concepts</h2>
  
  <h4 class="section-title">1ï¸âƒ£ What is an API?</h4>
  <p>An API (Application Programming Interface) allows two systems to communicate. It defines methods, parameters, and response formats.</p>

  <h4 class="section-title">2ï¸âƒ£ Types of API Testing</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Functional Testing â€“ Verify API functionality</li>
    <li>Positive/Negative Testing â€“ Valid & invalid inputs</li>
    <li>Load & Performance Testing â€“ Stress & speed</li>
    <li>Security Testing â€“ Auth, encryption, access control</li>
    <li>Validation Testing â€“ Response structure & data</li>
  </ul>

  <h4 class="section-title">3ï¸âƒ£ Common HTTP Methods</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>GET â†’ Fetch data</li>
    <li>POST â†’ Create data</li>
    <li>PUT â†’ Update existing data</li>
    <li>DELETE â†’ Remove data</li>
  </ul>

  <h4 class="section-title">4ï¸âƒ£ API Response Codes</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>200 OK â€“ Success</li>
    <li>201 Created â€“ Resource created</li>
    <li>400 Bad Request â€“ Validation error / wrong input</li>
    <li>401 Unauthorized â€“ Auth failed</li>
    <li>404 Not Found â€“ Resource missing</li>
    <li>500 Internal Server Error</li>
  </ul>

  <h4 class="section-title">5ï¸âƒ£ What to Test in an API?</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>URL correctness & endpoints</li>
    <li>Headers, Auth tokens, Content-Type</li>
    <li>Request body validation</li>
    <li>Response structure & time</li>
    <li>Error messages & codes</li>
  </ul>

  <h4 class="section-title">6ï¸âƒ£ Tools for API Testing</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Postman â€“ Manual & automated testing</li>
    <li>Swagger â€“ API docs & try-out</li>
    <li>Rest Assured â€“ Java-based automation</li>
    <li>JMeter â€“ Load & performance</li>
    <li>Newman â€“ CLI execution for Postman collections</li>
  </ul>

  <h4 class="section-title">7ï¸âƒ£ JSON Structure Example</h4>
  <pre class="p-2 bg-light rounded"><code>{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "Mithilesh Kumar",
  "course": "BCA",
  "status": "Active"
}</code></pre>

  <h4 class="section-title">8ï¸âƒ£ API Testing Checklist</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>âœ” URL reachable</li>
    <li>âœ” Correct status codes</li>
    <li>âœ” Mandatory fields validated</li>
    <li>âœ” Error handling correct</li>
    <li>âœ” Auth token required or not</li>
    <li>âœ” Database updates verified</li>
  </ul>

  <h4 class="section-title">9ï¸âƒ£ Automated Assertions in Postman</h4>
  <pre class="p-2 bg-light rounded"><code>// Status code check
pm.test("Status code is 200", () => { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });

// Validate JSON fields
pm.test("Response has id & name", () => {
  const json = pm.response.json();
  pm.expect(json.id).to.exist;
  pm.expect(json.name).to.exist;
});

// Response time check
pm.test("Response time < 500ms", () => {
  pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(500);
});
</code></pre>

  <h4 class="section-title">ğŸ”Ÿ Endpoint-Specific Scripts</h4>
  <p>Use these inside Postman <b>Tests</b> tab:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>POST /add â€“ Check 200/201 & validate created student</li>
    <li>GET /{id} â€“ Validate fields exist</li>
    <li>PUT /update/{id} â€“ Verify updated values</li>
    <li>DELETE soft/hard â€“ Verify removal & messages</li>
    <li>GET /list â€“ Check array & pagination</li>
    <li>PUT /restore/{id} â€“ Verify restore success</li>
  </ul>
